Read an interval in a controlled manner (input two integers in separate lines, where the lower bound is smaller than the upper bound). Then, within this interval, find the friendly number pairs. 
In case of incorrect input, print: Invalid input.
For friendly number pairs, the sum of proper divisors of one number equals the other number, and vice versa. E.g.: (220, 284), (1184, 1210), (2620, 2924), (5020, 5564), (6232, 6368).

Example input:
1
500
Example output:
(220, 284)

Tests:
InvalidInput_interval_test
• Inputs:
7
2
500
• Expected output: Invalid input (included)
InvalidInput_nan_test
• Inputs:
a
5
500
• Expected output: Invalid input (included)
